        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 12:31AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 1230 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mocksville, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winston-Salem, High Point, Thomasville, Kernersville, Clemmons,
Bermuda Run, Lewisville, Jamestown, Oak Hollow Marina, and Arcadia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
